post_text: Thank you Journey Church for this resource to students!
shared_text:
Journey Church
September 7 at 11:07 PM ·

Church, our staff and leaders are excited to open a new opportunity to serve you and our community in this unique time we are in, especially as it relates to schools.

Beginning this Wednesday (September 9), both locations will be offering a Community Learning Space for the month of September! This will include multiple rooms, free wifi, and an opportunity to learn online or homeschool in a space that is clean and created for you and/or your students. Space is limited so please view open times and reserve time(s) here: https://www.thejchurch.com/resources/

***Please note that masks are required indoors when with people outside of your family and when social distancing is not possible.

***Questions or would you like to be part of making this opportunity possible for others? Email office@thejchurch.com

post_text: Get Active and Stay Active by joining the Middleville Heritage Day virtual 5K/10K run and staying active with the Activity Bingo!
shared_text:
Thornapple Area Parks and Recreation (TAPRC)
August 7 at 12:11 PM ·

This year, the annual 5k/10k Heritage Day River Run is virtual AND it has two parts. Please sign up for this fun opportunity to support local youth recreation programming.

Part 1: For the run, you pick the time and the trail! When you complete your event, email us your time and where you ran (trail, treadmill, neighborhood streets, etc.).

Part 2: Complete an activity on our Get Active, Stay Active Bingo like hiking a trail or kayaking the river. When you complete a “bingo” you are entered in a drawing for gift certificates to local businesses.

The fine print: Registration is $25 for adults, $20 for kids under 13 years old, includes t-shirt and bingo card. Register by midnight August 15. You have until Labor Day at midnight to complete your run and as many activity challenges on the BINGO card as you like!

This event is our largest fund-raiser of the year. Please sign up to support youth recreation programming in our community.

post_text: Thank you Left Field Cafe for your generous support and help to TK Schools with your Face Mask Drive! We love our TK community!
shared_text:
Sarah Turner
July 29 at 12:47 PM ·

FACE MASK DRIVE FOR TK SCHOOLS

While our administration is hard at work developing their plans for the 2020 - 2021 school year, they've already communicated that plans for in-person learning will require safety protocols which will include the wearing of facial coverings (requirements will vary by grade).

Because of the importance of masks and the need for students to wear them, I've started a Mask Drive to collect new, reusable masks for TK's K - 12 students. Adult and kid size masks are needed. Masks can be purchased or homemade.

A drop box is available at Left Field Café On Main for your donations. All masks collected will be delivered to school admin to distribute as needed. Thank you for your support. Please help spread the word!

post_text:
TK School and Community Library is OPEN! The library opened today and will be open 10 a..m. to 6 p.m.. Tuesdays and Thursdays for curbside service. Patrons can pick up books that have been on hold and order or request items from the library. For kids, there are book bags filled with a variety of books per reading levels. Each week there will also be grab-and-go craft projects - this week kids can pick up all they need to make a really cool paper snail and a life-sized portrait! Summer reading signups and reading charts are also available to help encourage reading all summer! . Patrons simply call the library at 269-795-5434 and items will delivered outside.The library is located at 3885 Bender Road, Middleville.
Visit the TK School and Community Library web page at tkschools.org for more information. You can find more about searching for books and materials on the Lakeland Library system, renewing a library card or obtaining a virtual card, accessing eBooks and Audio Books, and finding reading resources and some fun learning activities.

post_text:
Dear TK Families,
Thornapple Kellogg Schools has offered free breakfast and lunch during this period of unprecedented closure. Meals service will cease for the summer months on Monday, June 29, 2020.
Monday, June 29 will be the LAST service day for Unanticipated School Closure Meals. We appreciate the support and help of our staff and community members and appreciate all of the families that have participated in this program. We wish you a wonderful and healthy summer.
As a reminder:
Meals for Tuesday through Thursday may be picked up Monday; meals for Friday through Monday may be picked up Thursday. Pick up times will be 3:30 to 5:30 p.m. at Thornapple Kellogg Middle School, 10375 Green Lake Rd. at the loading dock at the rear of the building. Please use the service drive to reach the loading dock area.
Pick up times will continue to be 2:45-4:45 p.m. at both Freeport District Library and Yankee Springs Meadows.
Thank you.

post_text: Thank You Middleville Rotary for donating gift cards to members of the TK food service and transportation staff who have been busy preparing and delivering meals to families in the district since the COVID-19 virus forced schools to close. THANK YOU Middleville Rotary!

post_text: Don't forget students and parents can get into all of the schools this week to pick up belongings. Tuesday and Wednesday. On Tuesday, students with last names beginning with R-Z are asked to come in between 8 and 10 a.m.; A-I from 10:30 a.m. to 12:30 p.m.; and J-Q from 1 to 3 p.m. Wednesday's schedule is J-Q from 8 to 10 a.m.; R-Z from 10:30 a.m. to 12:30 p.m and A-I from 1 to 3 p.m. There is also a scheduled time from 4 to 7 p.m. Thursday for any students at all buildings. Teachers have items bagged and sitting outside classrooms so they are easy to find. Students can return books and materials and high school students can also pick up yearbooks.

post_text: USS Hopper gives a shout out to TKHS senior Nicholas Bushman - and his future in the U.S. Navy! Congratulations Nicholas!
shared_text:
Life Promotion USS Hopper
May 12 at 6:26 PM ·

***We like to announce a new online initiative***

We know that because of the Covid-19 Virus students throughout the country will not be participating in traditional High School graduations. In a way to show our support we present to you the Life Promotion Presents: USS HOPPER Senior Shout Out.

In the upcoming weeks we will be making videos and “shouting out” some high school seniors who are awaiting to go to Navy boot camp. These future Sailors are going to have a little culture shock pretty soon so we want to give them words of encouragement and let them know they are not alone!

🌻Our first shout out is Nicholas Bushman of Thornapple Kellogg High School. 🌻

#StepUpWith70 #beamazing #classof2020
text:
USS Hopper gives a shout out to TKHS senior Nicholas Bushman - and his future in the U.S. Navy! Congratulations Nicholas!

Life Promotion USS Hopper
May 12 at 6:26 PM ·

***We like to announce a new online initiative***

We know that because of the Covid-19 Virus students throughout the country will not be participating in traditional High School graduations. In a way to show our support we present to you the Life Promotion Presents: USS HOPPER Senior Shout Out.

In the upcoming weeks we will be making videos and “shouting out” some high school seniors who are awaiting to go to Navy boot camp. These future Sailors are going to have a little culture shock pretty soon so we want to give them words of encouragement and let them know they are not alone!

🌻Our first shout out is Nicholas Bushman of Thornapple Kellogg High School. 🌻

#StepUpWith70 #beamazing #classof2020

post_text:
Online Enrollment For New Students is Open - This is basically a two-phase process. You will pre-register your child in the first step and receive an automated email acknowledging your pre-registration. Within two or three business days you will receive an additional email from TK Schools to complete the process.
There are step-by-step instructions to complete the process on the TK website under Enrollment. If you have questions or run into issues, please contact the building secretary for the school your child will attend.
McFall - Young 5, K and 1st: kschut@tkschools.org
Lee - 2nd and 3rd: adevans@tkschools.org
Page - 4th and 5th: dcisler@tkschools.org
Middle School - 6th - 8th: hdickman@tkschools.org
High School - 9th - 12th: mwert@tkschools.org
We appreciate your patience as we have built this new online system and look forward to you joining the TK family. http://edl.io/n1233768

post_text:
Congratulations Meijer Great Choices Film Festival Winners! TKHS students Ali Fiaz and Lena Braasch were named in the top 3 in their division and each received a $500 prize. Two other TKHS students, Jalen Oliver and Grace Densham, were each named as runner-up winners receiving $75. Teacher Jerry Robinson said this is an amazing accomplishment for all of them. Making it into the top three is especially noteworthy since there are only 18 videos out of more than 340 videos submitted making it to that status. Here is the link to the virtual awards ceremony today which also shows the award-winning videos by Ali and Lena videos!
https://player.vimeo.com/video/420421755

post_text: High school administrators took a few minutes to say hello to each of the students, ask them how they were doing and offer a thumbs up and a word of encouragement as seniors received their caps, gowns and other graduation items along with time capsules they created in middle school. Students never left their vehicles and social distancing was a must, but it was a great day with lots of honking horns, cheers from TKHS staff, and smiles all around! Great day to be a TK Trojan!

post_text: For three hours, TKHS seniors drove through the familiar parking lot of the high school - some with signs, balloons and flags adorning their vehicles. This was the first-ever drive-through senior cap and gown distribution for TKHS! It was FANTASTIC to see all these smiling faces again!! So proud of all these seniors and all they've accomplished! Congratulations TKHS Class of 2020!

post_text: Classroom Construction to Start This Spring - Construction of new classrooms at all three TK elementary buildings is still planned to begin early this fall, despite the current COVID-19 shutdown. And there’s even more good news. Costs for another aspect of the bond, renovation of the high school pool, have come in $1.3 million less than originally estimated without scaling back any of the renovation plans. This cost savings will allow the district to construct four more elementary classrooms than were originally planned when voters approved the $42.8 million bond last November. http://edl.io/n1224391

post_text: It's National Teacher Appreciation Week! TK is extremely fortunate to have amazing, dedicated, superhero teachers who are learning new ways to teach without being in their classrooms, finding new ways to connect with students without being able to be near them, and creating new at-home lessons for all their students. A simple "Thank You" hardly seems enough for all you do and all you continue to do! Your work and dedication to TK students is priceless! Thank you!

post_text: Update on Kindergarten/Young 5 Enrollment - The TK district is working very hard to create a new online enrollment system that is safe, reliable and free of errors. It is taking some time to make sure it works correctly and we will have it available as soon as possible. We know many of you are anxious to enroll your kindergarten and Young 5 students. We certainly hope the system can be operational within just a couple more weeks but we can't tell you exactly when at this time. We will communicate through many different means when the system is open and enrollment can begin. We appreciate your patience as we continue working on this new system to best serve our TK families. http://edl.io/n1220310

post_text:
A huge thank you to the Barry Community Foundation and the Thornapple Area Enrichment Foundation for working with TK Schools to create five drive-in WiFi spots for families without adequate internet service in their homes. This access greatly assists students who can now download homework information, videos, and lessons. They can also use these WiFi sports to log in to talk with teachers and stay connected with classmates. Please remember to continue social distancing while using these locations. We greatly appreciate the BCF and the TAEF for the support of this project.

https://4.files.edl.io/1360/04/28/20/162924-ec1a2d49-a644-441c-8113-361b0e4ade3a.pdf

post_text:
It's been awhile - but we want to congratulate our TKHS February and March Rotary Students of the Month - Sydney Purdy and Dawson Hamming.
Sydney is the daughter of Liberty and Thomas Purdy. She is a member of the National Honor Society, volunteers at school events, food banks, and blood drives. She enjoys dancing, reading, snowmobiling and working out. In the fall she plans on attending Central Michigan University to major in physical therapy.
Dawson Hamming is the son of Keith and Linda Hamming. Dawson has been a member of the TKHS baseball team and BPA. Dawson was part of the district champion baseball team last year and received the coach’s award. Dawson was also a BPA Regional champion. In his spare time, Dawson enjoys reading, playing baseball, and being outside. In the fall, he plans to attend college and study cyber defense.
Congratulations Sydney and Dawson!

post_text: A bit of TK history....
shared_text:
Thornapple Kellogg Alumni Association added a new photo to the album: Historical.
April 13 at 12:59 PM ·

Sara Jansens Klaasen , Class of 2003, found a set of notecards and shared them with our TKAA.
Remember, Union school was before Thornapple Kellogg (1931) and was located north of the Middleville Methodist Church in Calvin Park.

post_text: Painted Rocks Spread Joy - A bright yellow painted rock with a smiley face was placed by a mailbox. The next house had a blue painted rock with the word “love.” There were inspirational rocks placed at all 30 mailboxes in the neighborhood – all thanks to 9-year-old Sophie Lomakoski and her 11-year-old sister, Chloe and their family. http://edl.io/n1206925
